<item>
            <title>[SPR-13625] Support SpEL next to placeholders in annotation attributes (e.g. @Scheduled)</title>
                <link>https://jira.spring.io/browse/SPR-13625</link>
                <project id="10000" key="SPR">Spring Framework</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Currently The @Scheduled (fixdRateString) annotation supports property evaluations, however it does not parse spring expressions correctly.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The problem has been recreated at &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/rikitikitaco/schedulerSpel&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;https://github.com/rikitikitaco/schedulerSpel&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
            <key id="66517">SPR-13625</key>
            <summary>Support SpEL next to placeholders in annotation attributes (e.g. @Scheduled)</summary>
                <type id="4" iconUrl="https://jira.spring.io/images/icons/issuetypes/improvement.png">Improvement</type>
                                            <priority id="3" iconUrl="https://jira.spring.io/images/icons/priorities/major.png">Major</priority>
                        <status id="6" iconUrl="https://jira.spring.io/images/icons/statuses/closed.png" description="The issue is considered finished, the resolution is correct. Issues which are not closed can be reopened.">Closed</status>
                    <statusCategory id="3" key="done" colorName="green"/>
                                    <resolution id="8">Complete</resolution>
                                        <assignee username="juergen.hoeller">Juergen Hoeller</assignee>
                                    <reporter username="jdawson">Joseph Dawson</reporter>
